caption.title: Infection, dissemination and transmission rates of Aedes aegypti guadeloupe to YFV (IEC-4408, 1E lineage).
caption.p: Mosquitoes were exposed to an infectious blood meal with YFV provided at a titer of 10 6.5 ffu/mL. After infection, mosquitoes were examined at 7, 14, and 21 days post-infection. Error bars show the 95% confidence interval. In brackets, the number of mosquitoes examined. IR: the proportion of mosquitoes with infected body among engorged mosquitoes; DR: the proportion of mosquitoes with infected head among mosquitoes with infected body; TR: the proportion of mosquitoes with infectious saliva among mosquitoes with infected head.
